1
00:00:01,210 --> 00:00:03,780
(Episode 64)

2
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:33,200
I'm so scatterbrained,
I even left my phone behind.

3
00:00:40,350 --> 00:00:43,350
That's strange.
Did someone come in while I was gone?

4
00:00:44,180 --> 00:00:46,320
Why are the bedsheets such a mess?

5
00:01:08,910 --> 00:01:09,910
CEO Chae.

6
00:01:12,910 --> 00:01:15,350
I put some tea in a thermos for you.
Take it with you.

7
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:17,520
- Tea?
- Yes.

8
00:01:18,250 --> 00:01:21,490
What's gotten into you?
I'm surprised you could be so thoughtful.

9
00:01:21,550 --> 00:01:23,460
You've seemed tired lately.

10
00:01:24,090 --> 00:01:27,230
Who messed up these bedsheets like this?

11
00:01:27,630 --> 00:01:29,230
I was about to do the laundry.

12
00:02:00,190 --> 00:02:01,590
She left.

13
00:02:02,660 --> 00:02:06,130
Geum Soon, you knew?
You came to rescue me, didn't you?

14
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:07,570
I may not look like it,

15
00:02:08,230 --> 00:02:11,940
but I've been through it all.
Not much gets past me.

16
00:02:12,970 --> 00:02:14,210
Thank you, ma'am.

17
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:28,850
- Tae Pyung?
- Jang Mi, meet me at Baek Ho's office.

18
00:02:30,190 --> 00:02:32,790
Okay. I'll stop by quickly before work.

19
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:38,530
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

20
00:02:40,730 --> 00:02:43,970
Why haven't they called back?
Is he trying to make us sweat?

21
00:02:44,340 --> 00:02:45,700
Who the heck is it?

22
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:50,440
Who makes a threat and doesn't call back?
What's their endgame?

23
00:02:50,540 --> 00:02:51,540
Their goal...

24
00:02:52,510 --> 00:02:55,310
- doesn't seem to be money.
- It's not about money?

25
00:02:56,350 --> 00:02:57,780
Then what is the goal?

26
00:02:58,550 --> 00:03:02,450
I don't know. That was so long ago.
Why threaten us now?

27
00:03:02,490 --> 00:03:04,020
That's the mystery.

28
00:03:04,020 --> 00:03:05,160
And just look at what's happening.

29
00:03:05,290 --> 00:03:08,030
They call but don't demand any money,

30
00:03:08,090 --> 00:03:10,360
and instead, they want to play
this bizarre game of 20 Questions.

31
00:03:11,630 --> 00:03:13,330
Are they just trying to torture us?

32
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:15,300
Right.

33
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:19,800
Professor Kang said he thinks
Oh Tae Pyung is the one blackmailing him.

34
00:03:20,270 --> 00:03:21,270
Oh Tae Pyung?

35
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:26,110
Professor Kang and I both received
the same threats around the same time,

36
00:03:26,810 --> 00:03:28,780
so it might be the same person.

37
00:03:29,810 --> 00:03:30,820
No.

38
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:36,020
No way Oh Tae Pyung would blackmail me
with a video of his own father's death.

39
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:41,260
But it's suspicious that
Oh Tae Pyung suddenly showed up yesterday.

40
00:03:41,890 --> 00:03:44,360
Did he figure something out? Or...

41
00:03:44,430 --> 00:03:47,430
- I'll put someone on Oh Tae Pyung.
- Do it.

42
00:03:49,770 --> 00:03:53,400
Just in case,
find out if Oh Jang Mi has woken up.

43
00:03:54,010 --> 00:03:55,010
Got it.

44
00:04:00,980 --> 00:04:03,180
Still no word from that Director Kim?

45
00:04:03,850 --> 00:04:05,480
I'm going to check on it
when I get to work.

46
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:08,390
Did you get anything on CEO Chae?

47
00:04:08,590 --> 00:04:12,120
I tore her room apart looking for the USB,
but I couldn't find it.

48
00:04:12,190 --> 00:04:13,960
What would you have done
if you'd been caught?

49
00:04:14,030 --> 00:04:17,330
It's amazing you haven't been found out
in that house.

50
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:22,200
Before the accident,
Seo Rin and I switched places for a day.

51
00:04:22,830 --> 00:04:25,140
She trained me on every little detail.

52
00:04:25,470 --> 00:04:26,700
You switched places?

53
00:04:28,570 --> 00:04:31,480
So that's when you found out
about everything,

54
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:34,050
and why you were so devastated
at the Han River.

55
00:04:34,350 --> 00:04:36,680
You should have told me first, then.

56
00:04:36,950 --> 00:04:39,750
This won't do.
I can't leave you in that house alone.

57
00:04:40,050 --> 00:04:41,850
There's no telling what
CEO Chae might do to you again.

58
00:04:42,490 --> 00:04:44,820
I guess I'll have to get a job there
as a cleaner or something.

59
00:04:44,890 --> 00:04:46,260
What about your store?

60
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:48,190
You have to be the one
to protect your mother.

61
00:04:48,260 --> 00:04:50,760
He's right, Tae Pyung.
Please take care of Mom for me.

62
00:04:51,260 --> 00:04:54,800
You have to stop Chae Hwa Young
from pulling any more stunts on Mom.

63
00:04:54,870 --> 00:04:57,200
I'll protect Jang Mi. Got it?

64
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:01,210
Easy there. I can take care of myself.

65
00:05:02,170 --> 00:05:03,310
Don't you worry about me.

66
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,320
Wait, stop.

67
00:05:21,260 --> 00:05:22,330
Zoom in on that person.

68
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:27,200
(B3 Parking Lot)

69
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:30,270
That's not Director Kim...

70
00:05:59,830 --> 00:06:01,930
Okay, got it.

71
00:06:07,340 --> 00:06:08,770
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho?

72
00:06:09,540 --> 00:06:13,040
- Oh no, what should I do?
- I'll get rid of her. Just stay put.

73
00:06:15,310 --> 00:06:16,310
Lawyer Kang.

74
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:20,250
What? Director Ma?

75
00:06:21,490 --> 00:06:25,060
- What are you doing here during work?
- It's not time for work yet.

76
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:26,190
How can I help you?

77
00:06:26,990 --> 00:06:30,930
I was incredibly rude to you
the other day, Baek Ho.

78
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:32,230
I came to apologize.

79
00:06:32,330 --> 00:06:34,330
If that's all you came for,
it's not necessary.

80
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:38,870
Oh? Hong...

81
00:06:39,470 --> 00:06:43,010
Oh my.
Oh, I see Director Ma is here again.

82
00:06:44,010 --> 00:06:45,010
Again?

83
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:47,810
It's about a problem with the building
I got from Grandfather.

84
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:50,110
I came to get some advice.

85
00:06:55,490 --> 00:06:59,820
- Your tenant must be giving you trouble.
- Yes.

86
00:07:00,260 --> 00:07:02,590
I'll handle it just as you advised,
Lawyer Kang.

87
00:07:03,460 --> 00:07:05,660
- Let's go.
- But I just got here.

88
00:07:06,460 --> 00:07:09,570
- You go on ahead.
- Your desk is gone, so you're slacking?

89
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:14,040
- What do you mean your desk is gone?
- Oh, no, it's not like that...

90
00:07:14,740 --> 00:07:16,110
- Ma'am...
- I heard about...

91
00:07:16,110 --> 00:07:18,880
your letter of explanation.
Hope Mom forgives you.

92
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:20,980
- I'm so worried.
- A letter of explanation?

93
00:07:22,150 --> 00:07:25,450
What could our dear Hong Ju have done
to upset CEO Chae?

94
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:27,390
Gosh, seriously.

95
00:07:28,420 --> 00:07:31,220
I should probably come back another time.

96
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,190
Let's go, Director Ma.

97
00:07:35,890 --> 00:07:37,960
We'll see you next time, then.

98
00:07:56,650 --> 00:07:57,780
Oh, you're here, ma'am.

99
00:07:58,050 --> 00:08:01,750
- We've been slammed since we opened.
- You're working so hard.

100
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:05,260
- Wow, we're busier than I expected today.
- I know, right?

101
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:06,360
Oh my, that's a relief.

102
00:08:08,460 --> 00:08:11,560
The vegetables look fresh today,
and everything's well-organized.

103
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:14,670
I love that this place
has individual pots,

104
00:08:14,670 --> 00:08:17,340
so I can eat just how I like
without worrying about anyone else.

105
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:20,540
I know. And there's such a wide variety
of broths, veggies, and sauces,

106
00:08:20,610 --> 00:08:22,010
it's fun to mix and match.

107
00:08:22,410 --> 00:08:24,580
I'll have to make a reservation
to bring my mom next time.

108
00:08:24,810 --> 00:08:27,040
You were so worried
since it's your first time in business,

109
00:08:27,410 --> 00:08:31,080
but it's much easier following the system
from corporate, isn't it?

110
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:33,850
Tell me about it. I was so overwhelmed
because it was my first time.

111
00:08:34,220 --> 00:08:36,850
But since there's a solid system in place,
all I have to do is my part.

112
00:08:39,290 --> 00:08:42,630
The keywords for the brand renewal are
"a return to nature"...

113
00:08:43,230 --> 00:08:46,060
and "local healing."
We're updating the branding materials.

114
00:08:46,260 --> 00:08:50,670
For viral content, we're planning a video
on traditional therapy in the rooms,

115
00:08:50,900 --> 00:08:55,210
and we're also coordinating a shoot
featuring dishes with local ingredients.

116
00:08:55,470 --> 00:08:58,310
When the kitchen develops the sample menu
and holds a tasting,

117
00:08:58,680 --> 00:09:00,140
I will be in attendance.

118
00:09:03,510 --> 00:09:06,120
Okay, let's wrap up the meeting for today.

119
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:07,620
Yes, ma'am.

120
00:09:20,030 --> 00:09:21,030
Look here.

121
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:23,330
But that's a young man.

122
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:27,510
- There's no way that's Director Kim.
- It's Director Kim's car, though.

123
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:29,540
What about Director Kim?
Have you tried calling him?

124
00:09:29,940 --> 00:09:31,240
Apparently, at the Beijing branch,

125
00:09:31,540 --> 00:09:33,410
he called in sick
and didn't come in today.

126
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:34,980
His phone is off, too.

127
00:09:36,610 --> 00:09:37,820
What's going on with Director Kim?

128
00:09:38,620 --> 00:09:40,180
Something is definitely off.

129
00:09:43,350 --> 00:09:45,460
Seo Rin, what is it?

130
00:09:47,630 --> 00:09:49,430
Sorry, I forgot my phone.

131
00:09:49,990 --> 00:09:51,000
Please, continue.

132
00:10:02,210 --> 00:10:04,340
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

133
00:10:15,690 --> 00:10:17,890
Let's wrap up the meeting for today.

134
00:10:23,590 --> 00:10:25,000
But that's a young man.

135
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:27,600
There's no way that's Director Kim.

136
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:29,300
A young man?

137
00:10:34,810 --> 00:10:35,810
Right.

138
00:10:36,910 --> 00:10:37,910
Got it.

139
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:39,940
Just make sure it's done right.

140
00:10:44,580 --> 00:10:46,350
Honey, your tea is ready.

141
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:14,910
Honey, about CEO Chae.

142
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:18,450
She's been coming home late at night.
I wonder if something's wrong.

143
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:20,680
She seems to have a lot on her mind.

144
00:11:21,620 --> 00:11:23,250
She looked troubled.

145
00:11:23,550 --> 00:11:26,860
It doesn't seem to be about work,
but I can't figure out what it is.

146
00:11:27,290 --> 00:11:31,360
I asked Hong Ju,
and she said everything is fine at work.

147
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:34,270
It's so strange.

148
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:41,570
Could someone be blackmailing her?

149
00:11:50,010 --> 00:11:51,780
Sorry, I forgot my phone.

150
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:53,320
Please, continue.

151
00:11:54,990 --> 00:11:58,090
That's right.
It's been forever since Dad passed away.

152
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:01,990
What if they're only just now checking
the dashcam footage?

153
00:12:09,230 --> 00:12:12,940
It looks like something really did happen
to Ma Seo Rin.

154
00:12:13,340 --> 00:12:17,610
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

155
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,440
Yes, Baek Ho?

156
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:22,650
You want to get dinner?

157
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:26,080
Are you serious?

158
00:12:28,690 --> 00:12:30,650
Hold on, let me check my schedule.

159
00:12:32,820 --> 00:12:34,560
One, two...

160
00:12:38,260 --> 00:12:39,260
Okay, so...

161
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:42,670
Well, I have something,
but I think I can rearrange it.

162
00:12:43,130 --> 00:12:45,170
Yes, let's get dinner.

163
00:12:45,340 --> 00:12:47,370
If you're busy,
we can just meet another day.

164
00:12:47,510 --> 00:12:50,370
No, no, today works. Of course it does.

165
00:12:50,980 --> 00:12:53,940
So I should meet you at your office
after work?

166
00:12:54,350 --> 00:12:57,250
Got it. I'll see you later, Baek Ho.

167
00:12:59,850 --> 00:13:01,490
What's Baek Ho up to?

168
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:03,850
Why is he meeting Hong Ju?

169
00:13:06,790 --> 00:13:10,330
Didn't you say
you only had one class this semester?

170
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:13,430
So what were you doing at the university?

171
00:13:14,430 --> 00:13:16,370
I'm working on a research paper.

172
00:13:17,330 --> 00:13:21,840
Good. You need something like a paper
to keep you focused.

173
00:13:22,970 --> 00:13:24,610
I'm fine now.

174
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:28,450
So, is someone in there? A client?

175
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:30,080
No.

176
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,550
Our sons.

177
00:13:33,150 --> 00:13:35,320
I have a feeling
I'm about to marry them both off.

178
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:37,990
Here we go again.

179
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:41,490
I mean, Jun Ho, I can see.
But who does Baek Ho have?

180
00:13:41,630 --> 00:13:44,760
Didn't you say that Oh Jang Mi girl is
in a coma after an accident?

181
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:48,670
Baek Ho and Hong Ju have been
seeing each other a lot lately.

182
00:13:49,230 --> 00:13:50,230
Please.

183
00:13:50,530 --> 00:13:53,600
- They're probably just discussing work.
- Listen.

184
00:13:53,870 --> 00:13:57,110
That's how it starts!
First work, then love.

185
00:13:57,940 --> 00:14:02,110
Hey, why are you so loud? Keep it down,
they'll hear you in there.

186
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:04,110
Fine.

187
00:14:05,950 --> 00:14:09,190
You used to say you liked
my energetic voice.

188
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:14,660
You even said that's what
made you fall for me.

189
00:14:14,830 --> 00:14:17,360
Gosh, forget it!
What are they doing in there?

190
00:14:17,430 --> 00:14:20,260
You've been so on edge lately.

191
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:21,970
What's gotten into you?

192
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:23,900
I'm sorry.

193
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:28,410
Thanks for the tea. I'm going to head out.
Okay? Don't see me out.

194
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:30,170
Honey!

195
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:32,840
Really?

196
00:14:33,010 --> 00:14:36,950
Yes. If CEO Chae really
took your desk away,

197
00:14:37,150 --> 00:14:38,980
then that's a clear abuse
of her authority.

198
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:42,750
I know. But what am I supposed to do?

199
00:14:42,850 --> 00:14:46,120
What do you mean, "what can you do?"
What century are we living in?

200
00:14:46,190 --> 00:14:47,490
You can't just let yourself
get pushed around.

201
00:14:48,460 --> 00:14:52,000
Thank you, Baek Ho. I can't believe
you're this concerned about me.

202
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:56,670
Gosh, if I were the lawyer
on Dream Hotel's legal team,

203
00:14:57,130 --> 00:15:00,270
I'd launch an internal audit
of CEO Chae in a heartbeat.

204
00:15:00,540 --> 00:15:01,640
An internal audit?

205
00:15:04,210 --> 00:15:07,110
Where are my manners?
I got so angry for you...

206
00:15:07,340 --> 00:15:08,880
that I completely forgot
to bring you something to drink.

207
00:15:09,210 --> 00:15:10,210
Go ahead and take your call.

208
00:15:17,290 --> 00:15:19,360
- What is it?
- Found any dirt on Chae Hwa Young?

209
00:15:19,890 --> 00:15:21,790
You need to find out
who's blackmailing her.

210
00:15:23,260 --> 00:15:27,530
I've planted the seed with the Chairman,
so I need real information to follow up.

211
00:15:27,830 --> 00:15:32,340
Mom, if she's being blackmailed,
it must mean she did something terrible.

212
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:35,410
Oh my gosh, exactly. A crime.

213
00:15:35,610 --> 00:15:39,980
And judging by the way Manager Lee
and CEO Chae were whispering today,

214
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:43,980
- something is definitely up.
- Hong Ju, I don't know what it is,

215
00:15:44,210 --> 00:15:46,750
but I hope it's something that'll cause
a huge scandal when it comes out.

216
00:15:48,450 --> 00:15:52,360
- That's how you can get your job back.
- What?

217
00:15:52,420 --> 00:15:55,230
If they entrust Dream to Seo Rin,
who hasn't fully recovered her memories,

218
00:15:55,290 --> 00:15:57,560
the shareholders will never stand for it.

219
00:15:57,830 --> 00:15:58,860
Then...

220
00:15:59,730 --> 00:16:04,370
- I'm the only one left.
- Exactly. You're the only successor.

221
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:05,440
Absolutely.

222
00:16:07,170 --> 00:16:11,140
Ma Seo Rin losing her memory
is a godsend for us, isn't it?

223
00:16:17,610 --> 00:16:18,780
Geum Soon, what are you doing here?

224
00:16:19,380 --> 00:16:21,220
Don't tell me you were spying on me.

225
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:26,520
I came for sheets but heard you talking,
so I waited outside instead of coming in.

226
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:29,230
What would I have to spy on?

227
00:16:30,630 --> 00:16:34,230
If you want to work in this house,
you see nothing and you hear nothing.

228
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,030
So watch yourself.

229
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:37,530
Got it?

230
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:41,610
Just so you know, I was here long
before you arrived, Mrs. Yeom.

231
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:45,340
The nerve.

232
00:16:47,180 --> 00:16:48,180
Unbelievable.

233
00:16:49,580 --> 00:16:51,180
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

234
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:57,150
This is purely hypothetical,

235
00:16:58,190 --> 00:17:01,960
but if our hotel's legal team tried
to recruit you, would you be open to it?

236
00:17:02,330 --> 00:17:03,660
The hotel's legal team?

237
00:17:04,730 --> 00:17:06,300
It's hard to say.

238
00:17:06,530 --> 00:17:08,270
This is all very sudden.

239
00:17:08,900 --> 00:17:12,240
I can't give you an answer right now,

240
00:17:13,300 --> 00:17:16,540
but if it came to that,
I'd have to discuss it with my mother.

241
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:18,910
I see. I understand.

242
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:22,980
It would be so nice if we worked
at the same company, wouldn't it?

243
00:17:26,650 --> 00:17:29,750
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

244
00:17:33,790 --> 00:17:36,560
It looks like Yeom San Wol
is plotting something.

245
00:17:36,990 --> 00:17:39,100
Seo Rin needs to get her memory back.

246
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:47,240
Thank you, Geum Soon.

247
00:17:47,570 --> 00:17:50,510
(Thank you, Geum Soon)

248
00:17:55,350 --> 00:17:58,380
(Dream Hotel)

249
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,340
Are you okay?

250
00:18:21,770 --> 00:18:23,070
Are you okay? Let's get you up.

251
00:18:23,840 --> 00:18:25,580
I'm so sorry.

252
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:28,110
I'm not hurt, so it's okay.

253
00:18:28,380 --> 00:18:31,280
You were just working hard.
You don't have to apologize so much.

254
00:18:33,020 --> 00:18:35,520
I never knew Seo Rin had that side to her.

255
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:37,350
You're not hurt? Are you okay?

256
00:18:38,620 --> 00:18:39,660
Where are your parents?

257
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:45,400
They'll be here soon.

258
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:47,930
No parents would just leave
their child all alone.

259
00:18:48,270 --> 00:18:50,630
I'm sure your parents are worried sick
looking for you too.

260
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:56,910
I'll stay right here with you
until your parents come.

261
00:18:57,310 --> 00:18:58,310
I promise.

262
00:19:00,980 --> 00:19:02,080
See? You're not alone now, are you?

263
00:19:04,650 --> 00:19:05,650
What's your name?

264
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:07,250
Kim Hyeon Ho.

265
00:19:08,490 --> 00:19:12,090
Hyeon Ho. You're so brave,
not even crying at all.

266
00:19:12,420 --> 00:19:13,420
You're amazing.

267
00:19:15,660 --> 00:19:16,730
Hyeon Ho!

268
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:19,360
- Hyeon Ho!
- It's your mom.

269
00:19:19,430 --> 00:19:21,270
Are you okay? You're not hurt
anywhere, are you?

270
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:25,440
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

271
00:19:26,170 --> 00:19:28,470
- Bye-bye.
- Let's go.

272
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:36,950
Keep up the good work.

273
00:19:48,830 --> 00:19:50,260
Still no word?

274
00:19:50,590 --> 00:19:53,160
- No, nothing.
- Who the heck could it be?

275
00:19:53,630 --> 00:19:56,100
Who just makes threats
without demanding anything?

276
00:19:56,770 --> 00:19:59,440
Whoever it is,
they seem determined to torture me.

277
00:19:59,840 --> 00:20:01,910
I need to know what they want
so I can figure out how to handle this.

278
00:20:02,370 --> 00:20:05,110
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

279
00:20:05,180 --> 00:20:06,710
(Restricted Number)

280
00:20:06,780 --> 00:20:08,650
CEO, I think this is him.

281
00:20:12,080 --> 00:20:14,080
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

282
00:20:16,890 --> 00:20:18,790
It's me. Trace the call.

283
00:20:22,630 --> 00:20:28,130
(Restricted Number)

284
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:30,230
(Speakerphone)

285
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:33,070
Hello?

286
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:36,070
I'd like to begin our little negotiation.

287
00:20:37,240 --> 00:20:39,710
- Go on.
- 1,000,000 dollars in cash.

288
00:20:40,110 --> 00:20:42,810
- Bring it to a location I'll disclose.
- 1,000,000 dollars?

289
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:45,080
So it was about money after all.

290
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:47,020
Give me some time.

291
00:20:47,650 --> 00:20:50,290
It's not easy to come up with
that much cash on short notice.

292
00:20:50,490 --> 00:20:53,760
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

293
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:56,190
Are you kidding me, CEO Chae Hwa Young?

294
00:20:56,930 --> 00:20:59,460
You think I don't know
what Dream Hotel is worth?

295
00:20:59,830 --> 00:21:02,070
What, you want me to sell the hotel?

296
00:21:03,930 --> 00:21:06,100
I don't have that much cash on hand.

297
00:21:07,070 --> 00:21:09,110
Who just has that kind
of cash lying around?

298
00:21:10,510 --> 00:21:14,110
- Just give me a few days.
- I've given you plenty of time already.

299
00:21:14,410 --> 00:21:16,950
But you never asked for money.

300
00:21:17,010 --> 00:21:21,220
Chae Hwa Young, don't be so naive.
Are you playing dumb?

301
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:25,560
You've been around long enough.
Are you saying you don't know what I want?

302
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:29,290
- You should've been specific.
- How dare you raise your voice at me?

303
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:31,600
Don't you realize
I have your life in my hands?

304
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:33,500
All right.

305
00:21:34,630 --> 00:21:36,200
Just give me a few days.

306
00:21:37,530 --> 00:21:38,900
I'll call again.

307
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:45,880
You lost him?

308
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:48,880
Within a ten-kilometer radius, you say?

309
00:21:50,280 --> 00:21:51,280
Got it.

310
00:21:51,950 --> 00:21:53,980
How are you going to
catch him with just that?

311
00:21:56,190 --> 00:21:57,850
This guy is no amateur.

312
00:21:59,060 --> 00:22:00,320
Who the heck is he?

313
00:22:25,020 --> 00:22:26,650
You're not hurt? Are you okay?

314
00:22:27,380 --> 00:22:30,490
I'll stay right here with you
until your parents come.

315
00:22:30,850 --> 00:22:31,860
I promise.

316
00:22:35,590 --> 00:22:37,960
- What's your name?
- Kim Hyeon Ho.

317
00:22:39,260 --> 00:22:42,870
Hyeon Ho. You're so brave,
not even crying at all.

318
00:22:43,170 --> 00:22:44,170
You're amazing.

319
00:22:50,140 --> 00:22:51,780
I must be losing my mind.

320
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:55,210
Why am I thinking
about Director Ma all the time?

321
00:22:57,110 --> 00:22:58,250
This is ridiculous.

322
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:00,620
What's gotten into me all of a sudden?

323
00:23:06,420 --> 00:23:07,560
What are you thinking so hard about?

324
00:23:10,290 --> 00:23:11,330
It's nothing.

325
00:23:16,670 --> 00:23:20,100
If I join the Dream legal team,
I'll be able to stay by Jang Mi's side.

326
00:23:25,880 --> 00:23:27,010
Let me have one.

327
00:23:51,740 --> 00:23:54,140
- The money?
- It's ready.

328
00:23:55,210 --> 00:23:56,210
Hold on.

329
00:23:58,640 --> 00:23:59,840
Tomorrow at noon.

330
00:24:00,210 --> 00:24:04,550
Chae Hwa Young, I'll say this again.
You'd better come alone.

331
00:24:04,780 --> 00:24:08,450
Try anything funny, and I'll leak
the dashcam footage everywhere.

332
00:24:09,620 --> 00:24:10,820
Tomorrow at noon.

333
00:24:11,190 --> 00:24:12,660
He told me to bring the money
and come alone.

334
00:24:13,820 --> 00:24:14,830
Don't worry.

335
00:24:15,390 --> 00:24:16,790
I'll be right behind you.

336
00:24:17,660 --> 00:24:21,100
First, look into what I asked
and then call me.

337
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:22,470
Got it?

338
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:46,160
Tomorrow at noon?

339
00:24:52,660 --> 00:24:53,660
Baek Ho.

340
00:24:54,300 --> 00:24:55,830
I'm heading to the office now.

341
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:02,810
Someone is dead,

342
00:25:03,340 --> 00:25:05,140
and how can she be
negotiating a price for it?

343
00:25:05,810 --> 00:25:09,150
- Jang Mi.
- I was so furious I wanted to march in...

344
00:25:09,210 --> 00:25:10,610
and grab Chae Hwa Young by the collar,

345
00:25:10,950 --> 00:25:14,080
and demand to know if she's the one
who killed my dad.

346
00:25:15,390 --> 00:25:17,620
- But I couldn't.
- You did the right thing.

347
00:25:18,150 --> 00:25:20,960
Getting our hands on that USB
is the priority right now.

348
00:25:22,290 --> 00:25:24,460
So you don't know the location,
just that it's tomorrow at noon, right?

349
00:25:24,730 --> 00:25:27,930
Right. Must've told Chae Hwa Young
to come alone,

350
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:30,370
but Manager Lee will definitely
be tailing her.

351
00:25:30,600 --> 00:25:31,670
I'll tail them.

352
00:25:32,470 --> 00:25:33,470
You will?

353
00:25:33,570 --> 00:25:37,070
I'll follow Chae Hwa Young
and try to take the evidence from her.

354
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:39,140
Jang Mi, just in case,

355
00:25:39,480 --> 00:25:42,250
I need you to search Chae Hwa Young's room
and office one more time.

356
00:25:42,610 --> 00:25:44,010
You never know, there might be a copy.

357
00:25:44,450 --> 00:25:48,490
Baek Ho, that's too dangerous.
You don't have to put yourself at risk.

358
00:25:48,550 --> 00:25:51,250
This isn't just your fight, Jang Mi.
It's for my father, too.

359
00:25:51,450 --> 00:25:53,520
Jang Mi, don't even think about
facing this danger by yourself.

360
00:25:53,890 --> 00:25:56,990
Like I said, this is my fight too.

361
00:25:57,530 --> 00:25:58,530
Okay?

362
00:26:02,730 --> 00:26:05,940
(Dream Hotel)

363
00:26:06,140 --> 00:26:08,770
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

364
00:26:22,650 --> 00:26:23,890
It's a GPS tracker.

365
00:26:24,390 --> 00:26:25,760
And your phone, please.

366
00:26:37,130 --> 00:26:39,470
I set it up to eavesdrop in real time
so we can react accordingly.

367
00:26:39,740 --> 00:26:42,370
- You can't let him get away.
- Don't worry.

368
00:26:42,670 --> 00:26:44,310
Still no word from Director Kim?

369
00:26:45,780 --> 00:26:46,910
What about his son?

370
00:26:48,080 --> 00:26:52,850
He doesn't seem to have a clue.
On top of that, he's always wasted.

371
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:54,920
I have my guys in position.

372
00:26:55,190 --> 00:26:57,790
Good. Whether it's Director Kim
or his son,

373
00:26:58,220 --> 00:27:00,560
that video can't get out, no matter what.

374
00:27:08,230 --> 00:27:12,600
- Hello?
- So I finally get to meet Chae Hwa Young.

375
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:14,300
I'll text you the address.

376
00:27:14,300 --> 00:27:16,710
Bring the 1,000,000 dollars
and come alone.

377
00:27:17,310 --> 00:27:20,810
Like I said, if you show up
with the cops or anyone else,

378
00:27:21,040 --> 00:27:25,980
- I will leak that video. Don't test me.
- Okay, I get it.

379
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:27,580
I'll come alone.

380
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:29,320
Don't worry.

381
00:27:35,860 --> 00:27:38,130
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

382
00:27:42,270 --> 00:27:44,830
CEO Chae just got in a taxi
with a bag of money.

383
00:27:48,100 --> 00:27:50,640
Please, be safe, Baek Ho.

384
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:15,270
(The First Man)

385
00:28:15,330 --> 00:28:18,070
What do you think you're doing?
This wasn't the deal!

386
00:28:18,270 --> 00:28:19,270
Put that money down!

387
00:28:19,270 --> 00:28:21,270
Hey! Give me the memory card!

388
00:28:21,740 --> 00:28:23,370
Where's the footage?

389
00:28:23,370 --> 00:28:25,010
What was on it?

390
00:28:25,510 --> 00:28:27,510
Give me that memory card.

391
00:28:27,840 --> 00:28:28,980
My Jang Mi, you're here.

392
00:28:29,250 --> 00:28:32,350
It's me, Mom. Your daughter, Jang Mi.

393
00:28:32,350 --> 00:28:36,390
I missed you, Mom.

394
00:28:37,350 --> 00:28:39,360
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
